what i'm going to do is mention some of the obvious ones and as i go down through the body i just catch your reaction and the reaction of course is one of disgust now disgust is natural when it comes to taste if you put something in your mouth which is off then we should be able to tell us bad for us and we want to spit it out but disgust as a relationship

23
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:48,732
to the foul parts of the body that's something we learn and if you were in the medical professions of course you'd have to get over all that so i'm just starting at the top there tears wax in the ears so as soon as i mention it you see you've got to catch your reaction

