33
00:06:25,439 --> 00:06:30,024
Now we have another relationship to the body and that's to do with beauty.

34
00:06:30,564 --> 00:06:42,757
So often, unless you happen to be supremely beautiful, a Hollywood star or something, most people would not be satisfied with their bodies one way or the other.

35
00:06:43,517 --> 00:06:46,821
So just catch your face in the mirror.

36
00:06:48,163 --> 00:06:49,524
What do you say about it?

37
00:06:51,185 --> 00:06:52,307
What's your opinion?

38
00:07:01,331 --> 00:07:08,300
Can you change your view and just see it as holding virtually all your senses?

39
00:07:10,644 --> 00:07:17,531
That it's doing a job of work.

40
00:07:17,552 --> 00:07:19,855
And this is what we are born with.

41
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,062
Just accepting it.

42
00:07:31,302 --> 00:07:49,564
the importance is of course that we often have a certain be our self-esteem is often affected by how we feel we look in other people's eyes what about the whole body your whole body in the mirror

43
00:08:00,461 --> 00:08:01,583
Can you just accept it?

44
00:08:01,682 --> 00:08:02,803
This is the way it is.

45
00:08:05,007 --> 00:08:06,889
Be happy in your skin, as they say.

46
00:08:06,928 --> 00:08:20,002
So beauty is a social construct.

47
00:08:21,704 --> 00:08:24,127
It's we who decide what's beautiful and what's not.

48
00:08:26,788 --> 00:08:29,372
Can we lift ourselves above all that?

49
00:08:29,925 --> 00:08:34,532
and just see the body as an organism and that it's doing the job.

50
00:08:38,296 --> 00:08:39,758
The legs are to carry us about.

51
00:08:39,798 --> 00:08:58,701
This contemplation, you know, helps us just to accept the body as it is and of course as it grows older.

52
00:09:04,368 --> 00:09:08,313
The final contemplation is how much pleasure the body gives us.

53
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,625
From what we see, feel and so on.

54
00:09:17,708 --> 00:09:19,131
What do you fear the most?

55
00:09:20,693 --> 00:09:21,495
Going blind?

56
00:09:23,258 --> 00:09:23,839
Going deaf?

57
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:26,903
Paralysis?

58
00:09:29,107 --> 00:09:29,869
Something else?

59
00:09:43,905 --> 00:09:48,393
So now that's the fear of loss of something we're dependent on for happiness.

60
00:09:50,696 --> 00:09:59,408
But we know from people who are disabled that this doesn't have to upset their quality of life.

61
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:11,888
But for an able-bodied person to become disabled is a huge challenge, depending on how bad the disablement is.

62
00:10:15,765 --> 00:10:23,539
And there's the suffering.

63
00:10:23,559 --> 00:10:32,476
So using these contemplations to undermine this false idea of the body being mine, somehow I possess it, control it completely.

64
00:10:33,980 --> 00:10:35,783
But more the sense of working with it.

65
00:10:42,057 --> 00:10:46,822
The next contemplations are to do with coming to terms with sickness, aging and death.

66
00:10:47,884 --> 00:10:56,715
And these, of course, were so-called messengers from the gods that awoke the Buddha to his search.

67
00:10:58,235 --> 00:11:07,827
As the tradition goes, he was out on various days seeing a person who was extremely ill,

68
00:11:08,062 --> 00:11:15,991
one who was extremely old and a corpse, and an ascetic sitting under a tree suggesting that there may be an escape from this.

69
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:29,888
So these contemplations are really getting down to the nitty-gritty, the sense of identity, this body as me, I am ill, I am well.

70
00:11:32,130 --> 00:11:37,157
So just repeating these phrases to ourselves and accepting their truth value, that's all.

71
00:11:37,711 --> 00:11:39,052
Feel the resistance.

72
00:11:40,695 --> 00:11:42,437
Just let it be there.

73
00:11:42,456 --> 00:11:48,384
Just receive the truth value of these statements, repeating them gently to ourselves.

74
00:11:51,126 --> 00:11:53,691
This body is subject to disease.

75
00:11:58,316 --> 00:12:01,440
This body is of a nature to fall ill.

76
00:12:06,567 --> 00:12:10,072
This body has not gone beyond sickness.

77
00:12:18,543 --> 00:12:21,187
This body is subject to aging.

78
00:12:25,673 --> 00:12:28,879
This body has not gone beyond aging.

79
00:12:35,018 --> 00:12:38,384
This body is now in a process of aging.

80
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,024
This body is subject to death.

81
00:12:54,813 --> 00:12:57,499
This body has not gone beyond death.

82
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:05,929
this body will die.

83
00:13:18,663 --> 00:13:27,092
So now having undermined this wrong relationship of possessing and identifying with the body, we have to have the right relationship.

84
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:31,957
So the Buddha reminds us that this is a very precious rebirth.

85
00:13:32,679 --> 00:14:00,375
uh that here we have this combination of joy and woe and the intelligence to make our way out of it and of course you can't be here without a body it's as simple as that and it's through the senses that we experience the world that we learn everything comes towards us it's through the body we relate we communicate we express ourselves

86
00:14:01,705 --> 00:14:05,028
It's through the body we work for the benefit of ourselves and others.

87
00:14:05,769 --> 00:14:10,253
In this way we create karma, consequences.

88
00:14:12,355 --> 00:14:19,541
